snippet.title: Man dies in western Sydney crash
snippet.content: A man has died following a two-car crash in western Sydney. The accident occurred on the Great Western Highway in Minchinbury at about 8.20pm Friday. The 54-year-old male driver of one car was was treated by paramedics but died at the scene. The other driver, a 58-year-old man, was also treated by paramedics and taken to Mt Druitt Hospital for mandatory testing. (C) AAP 2017
